news.title: Developers eye new hotspots on Noida Expressway
news.para: The Max Group has also acquired a land parcel recently, while Mumbai's Oberoi Realty is also eyeing a plot in this micro market as its entry into the NCR (National Capital Region). On the Noida Expressway, developers such as Saya, Paras, Gulshan and Gaurs have launched projects recently, while Max has also acquired land in the region.

news.title: Kolkata: Online land auction to select builders for knowledge-based theme township
news.para: State officials said the plan is to select a developer through e-auction by KMDA in December. KMDA has floated an expression of interest inviting applications to participate in the auction.

news.title: CIDCO launches 7,849 affordable flats in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Under the Mass Housing Scheme, 7,849 affordable apartments have been made available to citizens from the economically weaker section (EWS) at Bamandongari, Kharkopar (east) 2A, Kharkopar (east) 2B and Kharkopar (east) P3 in Ulwe node of Navi Mumbai.

news.title: Diwali sale: Rs 139 crore off on Ahmedabad's SG Road plot
news.para: The plot, owned by Gujarat Institute of Chemical Technology Trust (GICTT), is located right opposite Zydus hospital in Thaltej and identified as survey number 94(a), final plot 5/1. Last September, GICTT had quoted a base price of Rs 385 crore for the same plot.

news.title: Asian Paints leases over 1.2 lakh sq ft of office space in Mumbai
news.para: Asian Paints has leased the space for a total tenure of nine years including a lock-in period of five years. The paints major is expected to pay more than ₹166.32 crore as rentals over the total tenure of the lease excluding any rental escalations and maintenance charges.

news.title: Puravankara's sales bookings up 43% to record Rs 1,306 crore in Apr-Sep 2022
news.para: According to an operational update, the company's sales bookings in volume terms rose 32 per cent to 1.76 million square feet during the first six months of this fiscal, from 1.33 million square feet in the year-ago period.

news.title: China new home prices fall 1.5% year-on-year in September 2022
news.para: New home prices in September fell 0.2% month-on-month after a 0.3% drop in August, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data released on Monday.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 2.7 crore from property tax defaulters in three days
news.para: NMC has engaged drummers, who are playing the drums in front of the houses of property taxpayers' defaulters since October 17. The drive is to be held at regular intervals until March end of next year.

news.title: Chennai: Kanchi, Chengalpet among new town development areas
news.para: The purpose of declaring the growth centres is to ensure wider roads, better traffic infrastructure and balanced growth in housing, commercial and industrial sectors, among others.

news.title: Sand crisis to linger on as 600 blocks await allotment in Jharkhand
news.para: Even though the annual ban on sand mining, which is imposed in adherence to the guidelines of NGT between June 10 and October 15 each year, has ended, the sand crisis in the state is likely to linger on as the mining operations have resumed in only 21 out of 622 sand blocks.

news.title: DLF sells housing units worth Rs 4,092 crore in Apr-Sep 2022
news.para: DLF Ltd has given guidance of sales bookings at Rs 8,000 crore for the current 2022-23 financial year, a 10 per cent increase from the previous fiscal. Its sales bookings rose to Rs 7,273 crore in 2021-22 fiscal from Rs 3,084 crore in the previous year.

news.title: Goa government floats Rs 11 crore tender for beachside co-working spaces
news.para: The department has identified locations for the co-working hubs at Miramar, Morjim, Ashwem, Mandrem, and Benaulim beaches. After developing the same, the government will engage an operator to run them.

news.title: Consolidation in real estate gathers momentum; listed companies lap up growth opportunities
news.para: The trend is getting accelerated as access to liquidity in the current market environment, where bond yields have already firmed up and continue to head north, is turning out to be a key factor in determining delivery timelines, a concern for homebuyers.

news.title: Extension work of Jaipur Metro to begin soon, says Rajasthan CM
news.para: “I know that Line 1 of Jaipur Metro needs to be extended. Soon the extension work will get started,” said Ashok Gehlot during a programme of Rajasthan Housing Board on Friday.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh showcases housing program on national platform
news.para: According to officials, the 30 lakh houses will come up on 71,811 acres distributed to the beneficiaries in Andhra Pradesh. The state government is spending about Rs.3,525 crore on layout development and Rs 32,900 crore on infrastructure creation.
